data.name: Cherrim

abilities.name: Spring Bloom
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't have a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).

data.flavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

data.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Big Bite
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Triple Whip
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

data.name: Durant

attacks.name: Devour
attacks.text: For each of your Durant in play, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

data.name: Scatterbug

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

data.name: Spewpa

attacks.name: Grass Cocooning
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The beaks of birds can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

data.name: Vivillon

attacks.name: Vital Powder
attacks.text: Heal all damage from 2 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

data.name: Fomantis

attacks.name: Continuous Slash
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

data.name: Lurantis

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

data.name: Tapu Bulu

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Nature's Judgment
attacks.text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

data.name: Blipbug
data.flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

data.name: Flapple V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Sour Spit
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks cost ColorlessColorless more.

data.name: Flapple VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: G-Max Rolling
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

data.name: Entei

attacks.name: Heat Dash
attacks.text: You may attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

data.name: Victini V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: V Bullet
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Flare Shot
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Victini VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Spreading Flames
attacks.text: Attach up to 3 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Max Victory
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.name: Tepig
data.flavorText: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

data.name: Pignite
data.flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

data.name: Emboar

abilities.name: Fighting Fury Stance
abilities.text: Your Single Strike Pokémon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

data.name: Heatmor

attacks.name: Burning Licks
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

data.name: Salandit

attacks.name: Call Sign
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.

data.name: Salazzle

attacks.name: Perplex
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Derisive Roasting
attacks.text: This attack does 90 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

data.name: Sizzlipede

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.flavorText: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

data.name: Centiskorch

abilities.name: Overheater
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent flips a coin for their Burned Pokémon during Pokémon Checkup, it doesn't recover from that Special Condition even if the result is heads.

attacks.name: Bursting Inferno
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.flavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

data.name: Horsea

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

data.flavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

data.name: Seadra
data.flavorText: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

data.name: Kingdra

abilities.name: Deep Sea King
abilities.text: When your Active Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, you may move any amount of Water Energy from that Pokémon to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Aqua Burst
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.

data.name: Galarian Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Find It
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.

data.name: Galarian Mr. Rime

attacks.name: Ball Juggling
attacks.text: Discard any number of Item cards that have the word "Ball" in their name from your hand. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.flavorText: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

data.name: Remoraid
data.flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

data.name: Octillery

abilities.name: Rapid Strike Search
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Rapid Strike card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can't use more than 1 Rapid Strike Search Ability each turn.

data.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

data.name: Corphish

attacks.name: Bubble Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

data.name: Crawdaunt

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

data.flavorText: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

data.name: Empoleon V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Emperor's Eyes
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Basic Pokémon in play have no Abilities, except for Pokémon with a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).

attacks.name: Swirling Slice
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Frillish

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon and heal all damage from it.

data.flavorText: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

data.name: Jellicent

attacks.name: Sediment Sink
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each Water Energy card in your discard pile.

data.flavorText: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

data.name: Bruxish
data.flavorText: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

data.name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Haymaker
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Haymaker.

data.flavorText: While it's often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.

data.name: Electivire

attacks.name: Tumbling Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Lightning Slam
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Lightning Slam.

data.flavorText: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

data.name: Shinx
data.flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

data.name: Luxio

attacks.name: Jumping Kick
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

data.name: Luxray

attacks.name: Electrostep
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Scar Strikes
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

data.flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

data.name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

data.name: Tapu Koko V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Spiral Thunder
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

data.name: Tapu Koko VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Max Shock
attacks.text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, their Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Yamper

abilities.name: Ball Search
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may put a Poké Ball card, a Great Ball card, or 1 of each from your discard pile into your hand.

data.flavorText: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

data.name: Boltund

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Defiant Spark
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack can be used for Lightning.

data.flavorText: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

data.name: Galarian Slowpoke

attacks.name: Tantailizing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

data.name: Spoink
data.flavorText: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

data.name: Grumpig

attacks.name: Dazzle Dance
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

data.name: Baltoy

attacks.name: Self-Destruct
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

data.name: Claydol

attacks.name: Power Split
attacks.text: Attach Psychic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like until your Pokémon and your opponent's Pokémon have the same total amount of Energy attached.

data.flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

data.name: Chimecho

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Pleasant Tone
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

data.name: Espurr

attacks.name: Focused Wish
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can't be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.

data.name: Meowstic

abilities.name: Ear Moves
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

data.name: Mimikyu V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Dummy Doll
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may prevent all damage done to this Mimikyu V by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon until the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Jealous Eyes
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

data.name: Necrozma V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Prismatic Ray
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Special Laser
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.name: Dottler

attacks.name: Radar
attacks.text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

data.flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

data.name: Orbeetle

attacks.name: Evomancy
attacks.text: For each Energy attached to this Pokémon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokémon, except Orbeetle, and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

data.name: Mankey

attacks.name: Focus Fist
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Field Crush
attacks.text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it.

attacks.name: Steamin' Mad Strike
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

data.flavorText: The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokémon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.

data.name: Onix

attacks.name: Rocky Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

data.name: Cubone
data.flavorText: It wears its mother's skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it's clear that it's always crying.

data.name: Marowak

abilities.name: Battle Armor
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Bonemerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

data.name: Gligar
data.flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

data.name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

data.name: Timburr
data.flavorText: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.

data.name: Gurdurr
data.flavorText: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there's skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

data.name: Conkeldurr

attacks.name: Hammer Pressure
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

data.flavorText: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.

data.name: Mienfoo

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

data.name: Mienshao

attacks.name: Spinning Whip
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. Shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

data.flavorText: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

data.name: Rolycoly

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

data.name: Carkol

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Coalossal

attacks.name: Coal Cannon
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

data.name: Silicobra
data.flavorText: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

data.name: Sandaconda

attacks.name: Big Sand Cannon
attacks.text: Discard the top 6 cards of your deck. This attack does 60 damage for each Fighting Energy card you discarded in this way.

data.flavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

data.name: Falinks

attacks.name: Rapid Strike Squad
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Rapid Strike Pokémon in play.

data.flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

data.name: Stonjourner

attacks.name: Land's Pulse
attacks.text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Giga Hammer
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Giga Hammer.

data.flavorText: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

data.name: Single Strike Urshifu V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Laser Focus
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Fighting Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Impact Blow
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Impact Blow.

data.name: Single Strike Urshifu VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: G-Max One Blow
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Rapid Strike Urshifu V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Strafe
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Rapid Strike Urshifu VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Gale Thrust
attacks.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

attacks.name: G-Max Rapid Flow
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Zubat

attacks.name: Hide in Shadows
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Their skin is so thin that they'll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another's bodies.

data.name: Golbat

abilities.name: Discreet Draw
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Air Slash
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in one go. They have been known to drink so much blood that they can no longer fly.

data.name: Crobat

abilities.name: Drastic Draw
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.

data.flavorText: It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can't drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.

data.name: Galarian Slowbro

attacks.name: Splattering Poison
attacks.text: Both Active Pokémon are now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Unhinged Hammer
attacks.text: If this Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

data.name: Murkrow

attacks.name: Scout
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

data.flavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

data.name: Honchkrow

abilities.name: Insomnia
abilities.text: This Pokémon can't be Asleep.

attacks.name: Voltage Dive
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

data.name: Houndour
data.flavorText: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

data.name: Houndoom

abilities.name: Single Strike Roar
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Single Strike Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Single Strike Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

data.name: Tyranitar V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Cragalanche
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Single Strike Crush
attacks.text: Discard the top 4 cards of your deck.

data.name: Morpeko

attacks.name: Gather Food
attacks.text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Hangry Tackle
attacks.text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.

data.name: Steelix

attacks.name: Steel Swing
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

data.name: Mawile

attacks.name: Powerful Vise
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Piercing Strike
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

data.name: Bronzor
data.flavorText: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.

data.name: Bronzong

abilities.name: Metal Transfer
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Metal Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.

data.name: Pawniard

attacks.name: Swords Dance
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Slash attack does 70 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

data.name: Bisharp

attacks.name: Steel Slice
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Metal Pokémon, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.

data.name: Honedge

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

data.flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.

data.name: Doublade

attacks.name: Cut Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

data.name: Aegislash

abilities.name: Stance Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may switch this Pokémon with an Aegislash in your hand. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokémon.

attacks.text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns.

data.name: Bounsweet
data.flavorText: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

data.name: Steenee

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

data.flavorText: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.

data.name: Tsareena

attacks.name: Tread On
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

data.flavorText: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon's legs leaves a wound in the opponent's body and soul that will never heal.

data.name: Grookey

attacks.name: Hit Twice
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

data.name: Thwackey

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

data.flavorText: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

data.name: Rillaboom

attacks.name: Wood Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Raging Repeated Strike
attacks.text: Discard any amount of Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 30 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.flavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

data.name: Zarude

attacks.name: Pack Call
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you go second and it's your first turn, search for up to 3 Grass Pokémon instead of 1. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Repeated Whip
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

data.name: Blaziken V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Blaziken VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Max Blaze
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 of your Benched Rapid Strike Pokémon and attach an Energy card from your discard pile to each of them.

data.name: Castform Sunny Form

abilities.name: Weather Reading
abilities.text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.

attacks.name: High-Pressure Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Stadium in play. If you can't, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!

data.name: Larvesta

attacks.name: Flame Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.

data.name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.

data.name: Volcanion V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dynamite Tackle
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has 10 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 150 more damage.

data.name: Scorbunny
data.flavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

data.name: Raboot

attacks.name: Volley Kick
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

data.name: Cinderace

abilities.name: Crisis Power
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Fireball Shot
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

data.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Wintry Call
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Melony cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Icy Wind
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

data.name: Sneasel

attacks.name: Cut Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

data.name: Weavile

attacks.name: Two-Hit KO
attacks.text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokémon is damaged by an attack from a Rapid Strike Pokémon, it will be Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Nasty Plot
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.

data.name: Delibird

attacks.name: Package Delivery
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck. If you do, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it's always scrounging around for more food.

data.name: Castform Rainy Form

abilities.name: Weather Reading
abilities.text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.

attacks.name: Rainfall
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: This is Castform's form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn't change to this form.

data.name: Castform Snowy Form

abilities.name: Weather Reading
abilities.text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.

attacks.name: Frosty Typhoon
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Frosty Typhoon.

data.flavorText: This is Castform's form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!

data.name: Snorunt
data.flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Froslass

abilities.name: Frost Over
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crystal Breath
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: It spits out cold air of nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.

data.name: Spheal
data.flavorText: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

data.name: Sealeo
data.flavorText: Be it Spheal or a Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

data.name: Walrein

attacks.name: Hail Prison
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

data.name: Tapu Fini

attacks.name: Smash Turn
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ocean Loop
attacks.text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

data.flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

data.name: Sobble

attacks.name: Keep Calling
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Rapid Strike Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

data.name: Drizzile

attacks.name: Bounce
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

data.name: Inteleon

abilities.name: Quick Shooting
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

data.name: Rapid Strike Urshifu

attacks.name: Rapid-Fisted Rush
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Rapid Strike Pokémon in play.

data.flavorText: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.

data.name: Ice Rider Calyrex V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Glacial Lance
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Ice Rider Calyrex VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Ride of the High King
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Max Lance
attacks.text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.name: Mareep

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You'll want to pet it because it's cute, but if you use your bare hand, you'll get a painful shock.

data.name: Flaaffy
data.flavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

data.name: Ampharos

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Searchlight Tail
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. If you find any Energy cards there, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.

data.name: Blitzle

attacks.name: Thunder Spear
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

data.name: Zebstrika

attacks.name: Coordinated Bolt
attacks.text: If 1 of your other Rapid Strike Pokémon used an attack during your last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

attacks.name: Spark Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

data.name: Thundurus

attacks.name: Assisting Spark
attacks.text: You may attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thunder
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

data.name: Zeraora V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Cross Fist
attacks.text: If 1 of your other Rapid Strike Pokémon used an attack during your last turn, this attack also does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Galarian Slowpoke
data.flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

data.name: Gastly

attacks.name: Sleep Pulse
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.

data.name: Haunter
data.flavorText: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.

data.name: Gengar

abilities.name: Last Gift
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Pain Burst
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.

data.name: Galarian Articuno V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Reconstitute
abilities.text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.

attacks.name: Psyray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.name: Ralts

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

data.name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Mirage Step
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Kirlia and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

data.name: Gardevoir

abilities.name: Shining Arcana
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and attach any number of basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Put the other cards into your hand.

attacks.name: Brainwave
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

data.name: Shuppet
data.flavorText: There's a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."
